	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65425659">This is why I avoided software that used an advertising Id.:  There's only one purpose in any Id. number and it's in the name:  To identify the device and thus, track it.
<p>
I avoided advertising in general:  Because it's an explicit hole in the device's isolation from malicious devices.  If a developer wants money he can sell his software.  Hell, for $5, he can issue a new product every year and demand another $5.  That's much cheaper than modern in-the-cloud products demanding $20/month.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_65425659">

